member.name: T:ESRI.ArcGIS.Geometry.ITransform2D
member.summary: Provides access to methods for transforming geometries using either specific parameters or arbitrary transformation objects (affine transformations, geographic transformations, etc.).

member.name: M:ESRI.ArcGIS.Geometry.ITransform2D.Move(System.Double,System.Double)
member.summary: Moves dx units horizontally and dy units vertically.

member.name: M:ESRI.ArcGIS.Geometry.ITransform2D.MoveVector(ESRI.ArcGIS.Geometry.ILine)
member.summary: Moves a direction and distance v. v can be in a different spatial reference than the geometry being moved.

member.name: M:ESRI.ArcGIS.Geometry.ITransform2D.Rotate(ESRI.ArcGIS.Geometry.IPoint,System.Double)
member.summary: Rotates about the specified origin point. The angle is in radians. The origin can be in a different spatial reference than the geometry being rotated.

member.name: M:ESRI.ArcGIS.Geometry.ITransform2D.Scale(ESRI.ArcGIS.Geometry.IPoint,System.Double,System.Double)
member.summary: Scales about the specified origin using seperate horizonal and vertical scales. The origin point can be in a different spatial reference than the geometry being scaled.

member.summary: Applies an arbitrary transformation. In particular, the transformation parameter can be either an affine transformation or a geographic transformation (datum shift).

member.name: T:ESRI.ArcGIS.Geometry.ITransform3D
member.summary: Provides access to methods for transforming 3D geometries using either specific parameters or arbitrary transformation objects.

member.name: M:ESRI.ArcGIS.Geometry.ITransform3D.MoveVector3D(ESRI.ArcGIS.Geometry.IVector3D)
member.summary: Moves the object by an offset defined by a 3D vector.
